## Conventions to preserve

- **Routes are thin.** They parse HTTP input and call a service. No business logic in route files.
- **Services own business logic.** They receive Prisma + ChppClient via dependency injection.
- **`asyncHandler` wraps every async route.** Never use raw `try/catch` in route handlers.
- **React Query manages server state.** Pages use `useQuery`; mutations invalidate via `queryClient`.
- **UI primitives live in `components/ui/`.** Domain components live in `components/` or feature sub-folders.

When adding a new file, update this document to include its purpose.
